{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"coaching":[{"coaching":"Plan how cross-story AC dependency verification sequence will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"block","finding_refs":["f6f036c8c1ede2c7e"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"cross-story AC dependency verification sequence"},{"coaching":"Pin down replacement reference verification in migration ACs with a concrete worked example.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["fefe1425f25423224"],"move_id":"6","move_name":"specification by example","subject":"replacement reference verification in migration ACs"},{"coaching":"Pin down replacement text for LLM routing and prompt files with a concrete worked example.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f6824b30e8cad96d1"],"move_id":"6","move_name":"specification by example","subject":"replacement text for LLM routing and prompt files"},{"coaching":"Plan how config comment content acceptance criteria will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["feea845e76be41121","f294446c38ace147c"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"config comment content acceptance criteria"},{"coaching":"Plan how S5 dependency consistency across plan sections will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f4465aa13496842ea"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"S5 dependency consistency across plan sections"},{"coaching":"Weigh at least one structural alternative for docs/experiments CLAUDE.md reference disposition.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["fdadacf621afbe44d","fc0f52e155962920c"],"move_id":"5","move_name":"weigh alternatives","subject":"docs/experiments CLAUDE.md reference disposition"},{"coaching":"Record an ADR for repo-level provider config version control convention — it reads like a one-way door.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["fb93d79ade9636de5"],"move_id":"8","move_name":"ADR / one-way-door","subject":"repo-level provider config version control convention"},{"coaching":"Weigh at least one structural alternative for dual tracked Codex config file relationship.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["fed99a5c0fc274fd1","fdfcfeccd709f6175","f13b524136ce544d3"],"move_id":"5","move_name":"weigh alternatives","subject":"dual tracked Codex config file relationship"},{"coaching":"State the concrete attestation evidence the [operator-attested] AC quality and completeness gaps will require (a change id / vote outcome / timestamp), recorded on the ticket.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f607dd457c67f9209"],"move_id":"14","move_name":"state attestation evidence","subject":"AC quality and completeness gaps"}],"coverage":{"counts":{"advisory_overflow":0,"advisory_surfaced":14,"blocking":1,"dropped":9,"indeterminate":0},"det":{"P1":{"ac_items":6,"blocking":false,"clarity_score":7,"name":"readiness-shape","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P2":{"blocking":false,"name":"resolution","probed":4,"ran":true,"references":4,"resolved":1,"status":"pass","unresolved_or_abstained":3},"P3":{"blocking":false,"name":"package-existence","packages":0,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P4":{"ac_items":6,"blocking":false,"desc_chars":4651,"file_impact":4,"name":"oversize","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P5":{"blocking":false,"children":0,"name":"task-dag","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P6":{"ac_items":6,"blocking":false,"name":"ac-quality","ran":true,"status":"fail","verify_commands_linted":64,"verify_lint_abstained":59},"P7":{"blocking":false,"destructive_hits":[],"name":"destructive-sniff","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P8":{"blocking":false,"budget_tokens":868000,"name":"reviewability","plan_tokens":1186,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P9":{"applicable":true,"blocking":false,"file_impact":4,"name":"file-impact-coverage","ran":true,"status":"pass"}},"llm_ran":true,"metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":212.9,"llm_calls":29,"llm_ms":528762.6,"total_ms":529090.6,"verify_requests":27},"remediation":{"baseline":"sidecar","eligible":false,"reasons":{"code_unchanged":false,"plan_changed":true,"registry_unchanged":true,"sidecar_baseline":true,"within_window":true}},"routing":{"agent_tier":["A1","E4","G1G2","G6","G7","T1","T10","T11","T13","T14","T3","T5c","T8","removal-rationale"],"single_turn":["COH","E1","E2","E3","E5","E6","F1","G5","T12","T2","T4","T5b","T5e","T6","T7","T9","hedge"]}},"findings":[{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a story-scoped AC1 variant that proves only the 17 files THIS story owns are updated (e.g. `git grep -l 'CLAUDE\\.md' -- CONTRIBUTING.md README.md rebar.toml docs/architecture.md docs/api-stability.md docs/exit-codes.md docs/jira-sync-setup.md docs/llm-framework.md docs/releasing.md docs/workflow-editor.md docs/workflow-engine.md 'docs/adr/0043*' docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md scripts/jira-pressure-test/e2e_field_validation_probe.sh src/rebar/llm/plan_review/criteria_routing.json src/rebar/llm/reviewers/plan_review_T5e.md src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py | wc -l | xargs test 0 -eq`), and demote the whole-tree AC1 to a post-merge integration check note.","cohort":["E2","E6","F1"],"criteria":["F1","E6"],"decision":"block","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'After this story (and its S1/S5 dependencies land), no CLAUDE.md reference remains in the tracked tree'","The proving command sums ALL remaining CLAUDE.md refs across the whole tree, including files owned by S1/S5 that this story does not touch","'Owned by other stories (out of scope here): docs/event-schema.md:46 (S1 replaces that pointer) and examples/claude-skills/{...} (S5 repoints them)'"],"finding":"AC1's proving command cannot pass within a single working session for this story because it explicitly requires S1 and S5 to have already landed ('After this story AND its S1/S5 dependencies land'). A developer completing only this story's 17-file edits will see the command return non-zero (S1/S5 files still contain 'CLAUDE.md'), making the criterion unmeasurable in isolation for this ticket.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f6f036c8c1ede2c7e","impact":0.85,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria, first bullet (AC1)","norm_id":"n503bb81642ac11c5","priority":0.7438,"reason":"high-priority+criterion-opted-in","scenarios":["An agent completes all 17 in-scope file edits and runs the AC1 proving command before S1/S5 land — the command returns non-zero, giving a false failure for this story's work","A reviewer cannot determine whether this story is done independently of S1/S5"],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"Add a new AC (before the existing AC1) that runs `git grep -l 'CLAUDE\\.md' -- <the 17 owned files listed in the plan>` and asserts it returns empty. Relabel the existing AC1 as an integration check that fires only after S1 and S5 have merged, or move it to the epic-level definition-of-done.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.875,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"low","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add or extend an AC that verifies the owned docs/scripts files now reference AGENTS.md (e.g., `git grep -l 'AGENTS.md' -- CONTRIBUTING.md README.md rebar.toml docs/architecture.md ... | wc -l` equals the expected count), covering replacement as well as removal.","cohort":["COH","E1","T4"],"criteria":["E1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["AC#1 script: `git grep -c 'CLAUDE\\.md' -- ':!CLAUDE.md' ':!CHANGELOG.md' ':!docs/experiments'` — checks only for absence of CLAUDE.md, not presence of AGENTS.md","AC#2 covers src/rebar/llm and docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md for removal only; no AC checks that CONTRIBUTING.md, README.md, rebar.toml, docs/*.md, scripts/*.sh now contain 'AGENTS.md'"],"finding":"The migration ACs verify removal of CLAUDE.md references for the ~15 non-src owned files but do not verify replacement with AGENTS.md, violating the E1 migration rule that criteria verify BOTH removal and replacement.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fefe1425f25423224","impact":0.85,"is_primary":null,"location":"AC#1 (global zero-reference check); What section (list of ~15 docs/scripts files)","norm_id":"n9001517a193dee6b","priority":0.5312,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A careless edit could delete the CLAUDE.md reference but replace it with 'docs/AGENTS.md' or 'AI_GUIDELINES.md' — AC#1 passes but the pointer is wrong."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"low","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify the exact replacement text for the T5e decision rule in `criteria_routing.json:407`, `plan_review_T5e.md:10`, and `docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md:467` — e.g. `'ADR / AGENTS.md / design-doc update'` if `AGENTS.md` subsumes that role, or `'ADR / design-doc update'` if `AGENTS.md` does not, so the LLM prompt and routing schema are left semantically correct after the rename.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["criteria_routing.json:407: `\"check\": \"A novel architectural decision is captured in an ADR / CLAUDE.md / design-doc update.\"`","plan_review_T5e.md:10: `…a novel architectural decision is captured in an ADR / CLAUDE.md / design doc update…`","Plan What section: 'the plan-review criteria text (both the src/rebar/llm files and the docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md mirror) references AGENTS.md, not CLAUDE.md' — specifies destination file name but not replacement rule text","AGENTS.md is agent-facing operational guidance; it is not an architectural decision log (that role was played by CLAUDE.md's design sections and ADRs) — so 'ADR / AGENTS.md / design-doc update' would be misleading to the LLM executing this criterion"],"finding":"The plan updates `criteria_routing.json:407` and `plan_review_T5e.md:10` (both active LLM routing/prompt files) to replace `CLAUDE.md` with `AGENTS.md`, but never specifies what the replacement decision-rule text should be. The current rule reads 'A novel architectural decision is captured in an ADR / CLAUDE.md / design-doc update.' Since `AGENTS.md` is agent-operational guidance rather than an architectural decision record, a naive find-replace would leave the T5e reviewer prompt and routing schema instructing plan reviewers (LLM and human) to look for architectural decisions in `AGENTS.md` — a semantically incorrect processing rule. The plan needs to define the canonical replacement text for these decision rules.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f6824b30e8cad96d1","impact":0.67,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/criteria_routing.json:407` and `src/rebar/llm/reviewers/plan_review_T5e.md:10`; plan AC bullet 2","norm_id":"n0271c102cbe76e42","priority":0.5025,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An LLM plan reviewer executing criterion T5e reads the updated prompt and tells an author 'record your architectural decision in AGENTS.md' — which pollutes the agent instruction file with ADR-level content.","The routing schema check field drives automated scoring; a semantically wrong target causes false PASSes on plans that correctly update ADRs but don't touch AGENTS.md."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"In the What section, add a note clarifying the canonical replacement: if `AGENTS.md` subsumes the developer-guide role (and thus is a valid place to record significant decisions), state that explicitly; otherwise change the replacement text in all three files to `'ADR / design-doc update'` (dropping the `CLAUDE.md` slot entirely) so the live LLM prompt remains semantically accurate.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":null,"blocking_enabled":null,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["P6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["1 criterion line(s) bundle multiple deliverables with 'and' (split so each is independently verifiable).","vague/subjective terms present: clean","verify command `[ \"$(git grep -c 'CLAUDE\\.md' -- ':!CLAUDE.md' ':!CHANGELOG.md' ':!docs/experiments' | awk -F: '{s+=$2} END{print s+0}')\" = 0 ]` has an unquoted shell variable ($VAR/$?) in its grep — it expands before grep runs; the pattern is not what you wrote","verify command `[ \"$(git grep -c 'CLAUDE\\.md' -- src/rebar/llm docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md | awk -F: '{s+=$2} END{print s+0}')\" = 0 ]` has an unquoted shell variable ($VAR/$?) in its grep — it expands before grep runs; the pattern is not what you wrote"],"finding":"Acceptance-criteria / definition-of-done quality issues.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f607dd457c67f9209","impact":0.4,"is_primary":null,"location":"","norm_id":"ned06ebc801a522e3","priority":0.4,"reason":null,"scenarios":[],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Split compound criteria, replace subjective terms with observable outcomes, and state how each is verified.","tier":"DET","validity":1.0,"verification":null},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Either add a note to AC#3's verification step confirming the comment reflects the completed state, or drop 'comment updated to the completed state' from the What section if it is not intended to be verifiable.","cohort":["COH","E1","T4"],"criteria":["E1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["What: 'pointing at AGENTS.md, comment updated to the completed state'","AC#3: only checks `git ls-files .codex/config.toml` and `git grep -q 'AGENTS.md' -- .codex/config.toml`"],"finding":"The What section describes a deliverable for .codex/config.toml — 'comment updated to the completed state' — but no AC verifies that the comment content is correct; AC#3 only checks tracking and pointer target.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"feea845e76be41121","impact":0.55,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — '.codex/config.toml … comment updated to the completed state'; AC#3","norm_id":"nb2ce53cb9c2ee668","priority":0.3438,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["The comment could remain stale/incorrect while AC#3 passes cleanly."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add S5 to the Scope section's dependency list so it reads 'Depends on S1, S2, S3, S5' and matches What and AC#1.","cohort":["COH","E1","T4"],"criteria":["COH"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Scope: 'Depends on S1, S2, S3'","What: 'S1 and S5 must land their reference updates for the global tree to be clean'","AC#1: 'After this story (and its S1/S5 dependencies land)'"],"finding":"S5 is declared a dependency in the What section and AC#1 ('S1 and S5 must land their reference updates') but is absent from the Scope section's dependency list ('Depends on S1, S2, S3'), creating a contradiction an implementer would have to resolve by inspection.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f4465aa13496842ea","impact":0.536,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope section — 'Depends on S1, S2, S3'; What section — 'S1 and S5 must land their reference updates'; AC#1 — 'After this story (and its S1/S5 dependencies land)'","norm_id":"n1fe60ebbf5ec7c40","priority":0.335,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An implementer reading only the Scope section would not block on S5, potentially merging before S5 lands and failing AC#1's zero-reference check."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Change 'Depends on S1, S2, S3' to 'Depends on S1, S2, S3, S5' in the Scope section.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"medium","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] State the intended comment text (or a minimum requirement such as 'remove any draft/WIP marker and reference AGENTS.md as the active guidance file') so the executor doesn't need to infer 'completed state'.","cohort":["E2","E6","F1"],"criteria":["E2"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'comment updated to the completed state' — 'completed state' is undefined; an executor must guess what the original comment said and what a 'completed' version would look like"],"finding":"The `.codex/config.toml` step says 'comment updated to the completed state' without specifying what content or wording constitutes the 'completed state', leaving the executor to decide what the comment should say.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f294446c38ace147c","impact":0.33,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section, bullet: 'Commit the Codex config: bring .codex/config.toml under version control… comment updated to the completed state'","norm_id":"n1fa3fd77ee2689e8","priority":0.2475,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Two executors produce different comment text; neither can verify correctness against the AC (AC3 only checks that the file is tracked and contains 'AGENTS.md', not the comment)"],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Replace 'comment updated to the completed state' with a concrete instruction such as: 'update the inline comment to read: `# Canonical agent guidance: see AGENTS.md at repo root`'.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.75,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an explicit rationale for the `docs/experiments/` exclusion — either classify these files as 'historical experiment snapshots not requiring update' (like CHANGELOG.md), add them to the in-scope update list, or assign them to a named story; do not rely solely on the ':!docs/experiments' AC exclusion pattern to silently absorb the gap.","cohort":["E4"],"criteria":["E4"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["grep confirms: docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/criteria/criteria_v7.json:465: CLAUDE.md","grep confirms: docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/criteria/criteria_v8.json:500: CLAUDE.md","grep confirms: docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/criteria/criteria_v5.json, v6.json, v4.json, v3.json all contain CLAUDE.md in the T5e documentation check","grep confirms: docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/harnesses/make_crit_v7.py:181: CLAUDE.md","AC proving command explicitly carves out ':!docs/experiments', confirming the author is aware of these refs","Plan scope section names three explicit exclusion rationales but none covers docs/experiments"],"finding":"The plan silently excludes CLAUDE.md references in docs/experiments/ (criteria_v3.json, criteria_v4.json, criteria_v5.json, criteria_v6.json, criteria_v7.json:465, criteria_v8.json:500, make_crit_v7.py:181) from all three named ownership buckets — 'this story updates', 'S1/S5 out of scope', and 'CHANGELOG historical record' — with no stated rationale. The AC's ':!docs/experiments' proves the plan's author knows the hits are there, but the plan body never explains why they are exempt. This is a silent scope exclusion that deletes work invisibly.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fdadacf621afbe44d","impact":0.33,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — 'This story updates' and 'Owned by other stories (out of scope here)' bullets; AC proving command ':!docs/experiments' exclusion pattern","norm_id":"n6daac2c00b415ece","priority":0.2063,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An implementer strictly following the plan updates the 17 named files but leaves docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/criteria/ with stale CLAUDE.md references — the AC passes because they're excluded from the count, but the criteria JSON files still point to CLAUDE.md when used for criterion authoring.","A future consumer of criteria_v8.json reads the T5e documentation check and follows CLAUDE.md (which will have been replaced or thinned), not AGENTS.md."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add a fourth exclusion bullet: 'Deliberately NOT changed: `docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/criteria/` criteria JSON files and `make_crit_v7.py` — these are frozen experimental snapshots; the live production criteria are in `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/` (updated above).'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a brief prose note (in 'What' or 'Scope') explaining that `docs/experiments/` CLAUDE.md refs are intentionally left un-updated (e.g. frozen experiment artifacts / historical snapshots) and that the AC deliberately excludes them via `:!docs/experiments`.","cohort":["G1G2"],"criteria":["G1G2"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["grep confirms: docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/criteria/criteria_v7.json:465: \"check\": \"A novel architectural decision is captured in an ADR / CLAUDE.md / design-doc update.\"","grep confirms: docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/criteria/criteria_v8.json:500: same text","grep confirms: docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/criteria/make_crit_v7.py:181: same text","Plan 'What' section enumerates 24 refs but does not list any docs/experiments hits nor explain why they are excluded","Plan 'Scope' section says nothing about docs/experiments","AC1 proof command contains ':!docs/experiments' without any prose explanation"],"finding":"The `docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/criteria/` directory contains at least three tracked files with `CLAUDE.md` references (`criteria_v7.json:465`, `criteria_v8.json:500`, `make_crit_v7.py:181`) that are neither listed in the plan's 'What' section nor assigned to any sibling story. The AC shell command silently drops them via the `:!docs/experiments` exclusion, but no prose rationale is given for leaving those references un-updated — making them unenumerated consumers whose omission is invisible to a reviewer.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fc0f52e155962920c","impact":0.33,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section (file enumeration) / AC1 proof command: `':!docs/experiments'`","norm_id":"n73da9479a47efcef","priority":0.2063,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A developer executing this story updates all listed files but misses the experiments-dir hits; the AC passes (due to exclusion) but live agents reading those archived criteria files still see CLAUDE.md","A future story sweeps docs/experiments and finds stale CLAUDE.md refs with no owning story to blame"],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"In the 'Scope' or 'What' section, add: '**Deliberately NOT changed:** `docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/criteria/` (3 hits in criteria_v7.json, criteria_v8.json, make_crit_v7.py) — these are frozen experiment snapshots and historical eval artifacts; the AC `git grep` already excludes them via `:!docs/experiments`.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a brief in-repo note (e.g., a 'Provider configs' subsection in AGENTS.md or CONTRIBUTING.md, or a lightweight ADR) capturing the decision to commit `.codex/config.toml` and `.agents/rules/rebar.md` and the rationale, so the convention is discoverable from the tracked tree without reading ticket history.","cohort":["T2","T5e","T7"],"criteria":["T7","T5e"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'Per-tool pointers: record the decision on optional ... Default: defer to a follow-up (none added here).'","'[operator-attested] The per-tool-pointer decision (default: defer) is recorded as a comment on this ticket citing the choice.'","The 'Assumption' section flags the provider-config commitment decision for team override but names no in-repo artifact that will persist the rationale.","ABSENCE: no AC or task step directs adding a note to AGENTS.md, CONTRIBUTING.md, or a new ADR explaining the committed-provider-configs convention."],"finding":"The decision to commit `.codex/config.toml` and `.agents/rules/rebar.md` under version control (rather than keep them per-developer) is a new repo convention, but the plan only records it as an ephemeral ticket comment. No durable in-repo location (ADR, AGENTS.md, or CONTRIBUTING.md) is designated to capture the convention and its rationale for future contributors.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fb93d79ade9636de5","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Plan section 'What' / 'Assumption (flag for override)' bullet; AC item 5 ('operator-attested... recorded as a comment on this ticket')","norm_id":"n4cd57dc432e8f1dc","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A new contributor clones the repo, sees `.codex/config.toml` and `.agents/rules/rebar.md`, and has no in-repo guidance on whether to add their own provider config here or keep it local — the ticket comment is not discoverable from the tree.","A future story modifying provider configs cannot find the rationale for why they are committed, making it harder to evaluate whether the same policy should apply to a new provider."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"In the AGENTS.md content (created by S2) or in the `CONTRIBUTING.md` edit this story already makes at line 570, add a 'Provider / agent configs' paragraph: 'The files `.codex/config.toml` and `.agents/rules/rebar.md` are committed so all clones and CI see consistent provider guidance. Per-tool configs (Copilot, Cursor, Gemini) are deferred; see [ticket/ADR link] for the rationale.' This turns the ticket comment into a durable in-repo reference.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","operator_attested":true,"prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Clarify the relationship between the new `.codex/config.toml` and the existing `scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml`: either merge the `AGENTS.md` pointer into the existing template (single source), or add a note to both files and to `docs/session-id-shims.md` explaining that `.codex/config.toml` is the repo-level guidance pointer and the shims template is for session provenance.","cohort":["A1"],"criteria":["A1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml already exists as a tracked Codex config template (docs/session-id-shims.md:91 says 'Copy scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml into ~/.codex/config.toml')","Plan adds a SECOND tracked file .codex/config.toml with different content (AGENTS.md pointer) targeting the same Codex audience","No plan prose explains the relationship between the two files or whether the session-shim template should absorb the AGENTS.md pointer"],"finding":"Adding `.codex/config.toml` to the tracked tree creates a second tracked Codex config file alongside the already-tracked `scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml`, with no plan guidance on how a Codex user reconciles or merges them — a config-surface proliferation risk.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fed99a5c0fc274fd1","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — 'Commit the Codex config' bullet; AC line '`.codex/config.toml` is git-tracked and points at `AGENTS.md`'","norm_id":"nf3d38476b74e3a81","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A Codex user following docs/session-id-shims.md copies scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml to ~/.codex/config.toml, overwriting the AGENTS.md pointer from .codex/config.toml.","A future story that updates the Codex session-shim template doesn't know to also update .codex/config.toml, and the two configs drift."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add the `AGENTS.md` model-context pointer (e.g. `model_instructions_path = \"AGENTS.md\"` or equivalent) directly into `scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml` rather than creating a parallel `.codex/config.toml`, keeping a single tracked Codex config artifact. Update `docs/session-id-shims.md` accordingly.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add to the What section a sub-bullet specifying whether `scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml` is retired, marked superseded, or kept as a standalone install guide — and whether `docs/session-id-shims.md`'s copy-paste instruction should be updated to reference the repo-root `.codex/config.toml` as the new canonical source.","cohort":["G6"],"criteria":["G6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan: 'Commit the Codex config: bring `.codex/config.toml` under version control (`git add -f`), it is currently locally excluded'","scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml already tracked: '# Copy this fragment into ~/.codex/config.toml (see docs/session-id-shims.md).'","docs/session-id-shims.md:90: 'Copy [`scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml`] into `~/.codex/config.toml`'","Plan does not mention updating or retiring `scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml` or `docs/session-id-shims.md`"],"finding":"The plan commits a new `.codex/config.toml` at the repo root but does not reconcile it with the already-tracked `scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml`, which `docs/session-id-shims.md` currently documents as the install template for `~/.codex/config.toml`. After this story lands, two tracked Codex config files coexist with no stated relationship: `.codex/config.toml` (loaded directly by Codex from the repo) and `scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml` (the copy-paste guide). The plan does not indicate whether the shim file should be retired, marked superseded, or left as-is — nor whether `docs/session-id-shims.md`'s copy-paste instruction remains valid alongside the repo-committed config.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fdfcfeccd709f6175","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — 'Commit the Codex config' bullet; AC#3","norm_id":"n9b0e4ba3d6f6ce87","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A developer following the existing `docs/session-id-shims.md` instructions copies `scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml` to `~/.codex/config.toml`, which may differ from or conflict with the new repo-root `.codex/config.toml` that Codex auto-loads","A new clone gets both files in the tree with no clear indication of which is canonical, and `docs/session-id-shims.md` still points at the old one"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Either (a) retire `scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml` and update `docs/session-id-shims.md` to note that the repo-root `.codex/config.toml` is now tracked directly (so no manual copy is needed for repo checkouts), or (b) keep both and explicitly document in `scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml`'s header that `.codex/config.toml` is the committed canonical version and this file is kept only for reference/manual-install scenarios.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Verify (with a doc link or spike result) the Antigravity `.agents/rules/*` import/include syntax before committing to a 'short reference-and-summary' approach — if `@`-imports or `include:` directives exist, prefer them to avoid a drift-prone duplicate.","cohort":["T1"],"criteria":["T1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan text: 'Antigravity `.agents/rules/*` does not support `@`-imports, so a short reference-and-summary, not a symlink'","No citation, no Antigravity docs link, no prior-art search in the plan","The assertion is load-bearing: it determines whether `.agents/rules/rebar.md` duplicates content or merely references it"],"finding":"The plan asserts 'Antigravity `.agents/rules/*` does not support `@`-imports' as fact, with no citation, doc link, or prior-art check. This is an unverified capability assertion about the Antigravity platform's rules format that determines the entire design of `.agents/rules/rebar.md` (summary+reference vs. a proper include/symlink).","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fe84c537fd7a5c3e6","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — bullet 'Commit the generic rules file': 'Antigravity `.agents/rules/*` does not support `@`-imports, so a short reference-and-summary, not a symlink'","norm_id":"n8e42ed18eae3977e","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["If Antigravity actually does support `@file` or `include:` directives, the plan's 'short summary' approach leaves a stale, drift-prone copy instead of a live reference, directly undermining the 'source of truth' goal.","If the assertion is wrong in the other direction (Antigravity ignores the file entirely unless formatted differently), the committed file provides no actual guidance to the agent."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a footnote citing the Antigravity rules-format documentation (URL or internal doc). If a supported include syntax exists, use it; if confirmed absent, note the checked source so reviewers and future editors know the constraint is verified.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.6667,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"yes","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Address the prior-art relationship between `.codex/config.toml` (new) and `scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml` (existing): either consolidate them (e.g., make the shim template a symlink or reference the new root file), update `docs/session-id-shims.md` to reflect the new canonical location, or explicitly state why both coexist.","cohort":["T1"],"criteria":["T1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan text: 'bring `.codex/config.toml` under version control (`git add -f`, it is currently locally excluded) pointing at `AGENTS.md`, comment updated to the completed state'","scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml already tracked, with identical shell_environment_policy.set logic","docs/session-id-shims.md:90 instructs users to copy scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml into ~/.codex/config.toml","tests/unit/test_harness_shims.py:22,65 reference and test the shim template"],"finding":"The plan proposes committing `.codex/config.toml` to the repo root, but a tracked `scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml` already exists as the canonical Codex config template, with documentation (`docs/session-id-shims.md:90`) and unit tests (`tests/unit/test_harness_shims.py:22`) pointing to it. The plan does not acknowledge this prior art or explain how the new root-level file relates to (or supersedes) the existing shim template.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f13b524136ce544d3","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — bullet 'Commit the Codex config'; also 'Scope' section which lists `.codex/config.toml` as in-scope","norm_id":"n956042294de84f76","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Developers following the existing docs/session-id-shims.md instructions copy the shim template into ~/.codex/config.toml, then git-pull and find a committed .codex/config.toml in the repo root that may differ — causing confusion about which is authoritative.","If `.codex/config.toml` at the repo root diverges from `scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml`, there are two competing source-of-truth files for Codex configuration, with no declared relationship."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a cited source (URL or ADR) for the claim that Antigravity `.agents/rules/*` does not support `@`-imports, or restate it as a 'believed' constraint to be validated before authoring the summary file.","cohort":["T3"],"criteria":["T3"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Zero occurrences of 'Antigravity' or 'antigravity' anywhere in the repo (search confirmed)","The plan names no docs URL, config reference, or prior story that establishes this constraint","Evidence class: Unverified"],"finding":"The plan asserts 'Antigravity `.agents/rules/*` does not support `@`-imports' as a known fact, but 'Antigravity' appears nowhere in the repo's documentation or codebase. This is an unverified capability constraint on an unrecognised external tool.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fbafa925622582a13","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — bullet: 'Commit the generic rules file: … Antigravity `.agents/rules/*` does not support `@`-imports'","norm_id":"n103cea4ebbf16611","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["If Antigravity does support `@`-imports (or file references), then the authored `.agents/rules/rebar.md` will be a hand-rolled summary whose content can drift, when a direct include would have stayed in sync automatically.","If 'Antigravity' is a future product whose import semantics change, the hard-coded choice may become stale without a recorded rationale to revisit."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Change the prose from 'Antigravity `.agents/rules/*` does not support `@`-imports, so a short reference-and-summary' to 'Antigravity `.agents/rules/*` is believed not to support `@`-imports (verify against [link-to-docs]); therefore a short reference-and-summary…'. If a canonical docs URL exists, cite it.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.6667,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"yes","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"sel