 — the key the plan describes updating. AC#3's proving command (`rg -n 'AGENTS.md|migrated' .codex/config.toml`) will fail or return nothing because the file path is wrong. The mechanism for this deliverable is therefore broken as specified.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"ff67482e53d4a257e","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Design decisions section ('Default: keep the fallback line but update the comment'); AC#3 ('`.codex/config.toml` reflects the completed migration')","norm_id":"ne713b85af1d3e980","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:cited-reference-inaccurate","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Change the plan's `.codex/config.toml` references to `scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml` and update AC#3's proving command to `rg -n 'AGENTS.md|migrated' scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml`. If `project_doc_fallback_filenames` is a real Codex key, add a comment in that file; if it does not exist in the Codex schema, remove that part of the design decision and note only the comment-update in the existing shim.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.4286,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"no","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["T3"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The plan asserts two unverified Codex CLI capabilities that are load-bearing for AC3: (a) 'Codex reads AGENTS.md natively as primary' and (b) that `.codex/config.toml` currently contains a `project_doc_fallback_filenames=[\"CLAUDE.md\"]` key with a 'temporary…until migrated' comment. Neither assertion can be confirmed: `.codex/config.toml` does not exist anywhere in the repo (no `.codex/` directory visible), the only Codex shim is `scripts/session-shims/codex-config.toml` (which contains only `[shell_environment_policy]` — no `project_doc_fallback_filenames`), and no search hit for the key exists outside cached prior-review artifacts. The Codex config reference URL is cited but not reachable for verification — evidence class: Unverified. If `project_doc_fallback_filenames` is not a real Codex config key, or if Codex does not natively prioritize AGENTS.md, the entire rationale for the AC3 edit collapses, and the AC3 prove command (`rg -n 'AGENTS.md|migrated' .codex/config.toml`) will error on a missing file.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fa60016b0f54011b1","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Design decisions section ('Codex reads AGENTS.md natively as primary, so project_doc_fallback_filenames=[\"CLAUDE.md\"] becomes moot'); Why section ('`.codex/config.toml` currently falls back to CLAUDE.md with a comment saying it's temporary'); AC3 and its prove command","norm_id":"n77f7e8e6248bd6a4","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Check the Codex config-reference docs for the `project_doc_fallback_filenames` key. If it exists and `.codex/config.toml` is intended as a repo-tracked project-level config, create the file and add it to scope. If Codex's AGENTS.md prioritization is built-in and requires no config, state that explicitly and drop the 'keep the fallback line' instruction from the design decision — the AC3 prove command should then target whichever file actually exists.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.4286,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["G1G2"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The AC2 proving command checks only `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/criteria_routing.json` and `src/rebar/llm/reviewers/plan_review_T5e.md` for residual `CLAUDE.md` references, but `docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md` line 467 contains an identical `CLAUDE.md` occurrence ('A novel architectural decision is captured in an ADR / CLAUDE.md / design-doc update') that the plan lists as an in-scope update target. After the edit, the AC2 command would pass even if the guide is missed.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f0970f28894ad0a16","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria AC2 — proving command; `docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md` line 467","norm_id":"n9e02cf635a1d4834","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:cited-reference-inaccurate","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Replace the AC2 command with: `rg -c 'CLAUDE\\.md' src/rebar/llm/plan_review/criteria_routing.json src/rebar/llm/reviewers/plan_review_T5e.md docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md | awk -F: '{s+=$